<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-24T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-24T21:00:00-05:00" n="133" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/512: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-24T21:00:00-05:00">October
                                    24, 1935—9 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>315. Department’s 313, October 24, 7 p.m. When conveying to the British
                            Government our acceptance of their invitation, you should inform them
                            that of course we are accepting on the assumption that the British
                            agreed to the position taken in our last cable giving the Navy
                            Department basis for agreement<note n="84" xml:id="d133fn84">See
                                Department’s telegram No. 300, October 14, 6 p.m., <ref target="#pg_125">p. 125</ref>.</note> and also, notwithstanding
                            the fact that it may not be possible to agree now on quantitative
                            limitations, that it is still to be understood that we both agree on the
                            principle of naval parity as between the United States and the British
                            Empire.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>